Isabelle Keith https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isabelle_Keith 0 Isabelle Keith (May 27, 1898, New York City – July 20, 1979, Mill Valley, California) was an American actress. She appeared in 42 films between 1919 and 1936, most of them from the M-G-M studio, and on two occasions with Laurel and Hardy. She was sometimes credited as Claudelle Kaye, Elizabeth Keith, Isabelle Keep and Isobel Keep.
